      "content": "Yes, it makes perfect sense to feel like you've already left because your life has fundamentally changed, and the person you were is no longer here to guide you. This sense of being a ghost trapped in a loop is a common symptom of deep grief, where the world suddenly feels too big and too empty for the person you are. You are not broken for feeling this way; you are simply grieving the loss of the world you knew, and it is okay to stop trying to fit into a house that no longer feels like home.",
